==Irish==

===Etymology===
Irish, meaning 'little [[Adam]]'.

===Proper noun===
'''Adamnan'''

# The name a Irish saint (c. 624-704), the biographer of St. Columba and a acquaintance of the Venerable [[Bede]].
# A male [[given name]].

====Translation====
{{top}}
*Gaelic: Adhamhnan (pronounced: Yownan)
*Irish: Ádhamhnán
*Scottish: Adamnan
{{bottom}}

====Variants====
{{top}}
*Irish: Adamnan, Awnan, Odanodan, Onan, Ounan, Junan
*Scottish: Adamnan
{{bottom}}

